00070 typedef struct _PIZBoundedHashTableElement {
00071     long key;                                           /* The key as long. */
00072     void *ptr;                                          /* Pointer to the item to store. */
00073     } PIZBoundedHashTableElement;
00074     
00075 /**
00076  * \remark  Bounded hashtable with \c long keys.
00077  *          Implemented with an array of dynamic arrays, and a pre-allocated pool of elements.
00078  *          To obtain the hash value : index =  key % size.
00079  * \ingroup boundedHashTable
00080  */
00081  
00082 typedef struct _PIZBoundedHashTable {
00083     long                        flags;              /* Flags as bit field. */
00084     long                        count;              /* Number of elements in the hashtable. */
00085     long                        hashSize;           /* Number of dynamic arrays in the hashtable. */
00086     long                        poolSize;           /* Maximum number of items in the hashtable. */
00087     PIZBoundedStack             *ticketMachine;     /* Ticket machine for pool management. */
00088     PIZBoundedHashTableElement  *pool;              /* Pool of elements. */
00089     PIZGrowingArray             **hashTable;        /* Pointer to the hashtable's array of dynamic arrays. */
00090     } PIZBoundedHashTable;

00097 /**
00098  * \brief   Create the bounded hashtable.
00099  * \details The function accepts two arguments : the size and the pool size. 
00100  *          The size should be a prime number, default is 157.
00101  *          Default pool size is 128.
00102  *          In case of failure the pointer is NULL.
00103  * \param   argc The number of arguments.
00104  * \param   argv A pointer to arguments.
00105  * \return  A pointer to the new bounded hashtable.
00106  * \remark  The following shows how to create a bounded hashtable.  
00107  * \code
00108  * long                    args[2] = {59, 100};
00109  * PIZBoundedHashTable     *myHashtab = NULL;
00110  *
00111  * myHashtab = pizBoundedHashTableNew (2, args);  
00112  * myHashtab = pizBoundedHashTableNew (0, NULL);  // default values.
00113  *
00114  * \endcode
00115  * \ingroup boundedHashTable
00116  */
00117 PIZBoundedHashTable *pizBoundedHashTableNew (long argc, long *argv);
00118
